#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Command Mode with Aesh"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"https://github.com/aeshell/aesh[Aesh] is a Java library for building interactive command line applications.\n"
"It supports option parsing, tab completion, command grouping, and an interactive shell (REPL) mode.\n"
"For more details about the Aesh library itself, see the https://aeshell.github.io/[Aesh documentation]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Quarkus provides support for using Aesh. This guide contains examples of the `aesh` extension usage."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "If you are not familiar with the Quarkus Command Mode, consider reading the xref:command-mode-reference.adoc[Command Mode reference guide] first."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Extension"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"Once you have your Quarkus project configured you can add the `aesh` extension\n"
"to your project by running the following command in your project base directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "This will add the following to your build file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "pom.xml"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "build.gradle"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"For optimal performance (especially in native mode), add the Aesh annotation processor to\n"
"your Maven compiler plugin configuration. This generates compile-time command metadata,\n"
"eliminating reflection-based annotation scanning at runtime:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"The annotation processor is optional. Without it, Aesh falls back to runtime\n"
"reflection for command metadata, which works correctly but is slower at startup."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Building a command line application"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"The Aesh extension supports two execution modes, controlled by the `quarkus.aesh.mode` build-time property.\n"
"Console mode is what makes Aesh distinctive -- it provides an interactive shell (REPL) where users can type multiple commands with tab completion and command history.\n"
"Runtime mode executes a single command and exits, like a standard CLI tool.\n"
"In most cases, the mode is auto-detected based on your command annotations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Console mode (interactive shell)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"Console mode starts an interactive shell (REPL) where users can type multiple commands.\n"
"This is what differentiates Aesh from other CLI frameworks: users get an interactive session\n"
"with tab completion, command history, and shared state across commands."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"Console mode is automatically selected when there are multiple `@CommandDefinition` classes\n"
"without `groupCommands`, when there are multiple independent commands,\n"
"or when a remote transport (WebSocket or SSH) is present.\n"
"You can also force it with `quarkus.aesh.mode=console`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "With two commands, console mode is auto-detected:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "The prompt, exit command, and other console settings are configurable via `quarkus.aesh.*` properties."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Group commands in console mode (sub-command mode)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"You can use `@CommandDefinition` with `groupCommands` in console mode to create command groups with sub-command mode.\n"
"When a user types a group command without a sub-command, they enter an interactive context for that group:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Sub-commands listed in `groupCommands` are only accessible through their parent group -- they do not appear as top-level commands in the shell."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Sub-commands use `@CommandDefinition` without `groupCommands`. The extension automatically excludes them from top-level registration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "CDI injection works in sub-commands. The extension injects `@Inject` fields after Aesh creates the sub-command instances."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "An interactive session using sub-command mode:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Sub-commands can be called directly with their parent prefix."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Typing just the group command name enters sub-command mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Inside sub-command mode, type sub-commands directly without the parent prefix."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Type `exit` (or `..`) to leave sub-command mode and return to the main prompt."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"Because `TaskService` is `@ApplicationScoped`, state is shared across all commands in the session.\n"
"This is a key advantage of console mode over runtime mode, where each invocation is a separate process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Runtime mode (single command execution)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"This is the default mode when there is a single `@CommandDefinition` or a `@CommandDefinition` with `groupCommands`.\n"
"The application executes one command and exits, similar to standard CLI tools."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Simple application"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "A simple Aesh application with a single command can be created as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "If there is only one class annotated with `@CommandDefinition`, it is automatically used as the entry point of the command line application."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "All command classes are registered as CDI beans. You can use `@Inject` to inject other beans."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"Beans annotated with `@CommandDefinition` should not use proxied scopes (e.g. do not use `@ApplicationScoped`)\n"
"because Aesh sets field values directly via reflection.\n"
"By default, the Aesh extension registers command classes with the `@Dependent` scope."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Grouped commands with subcommands"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "`groupCommands` lists the subcommands available under this parent command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "`@ParentCommand` injects the parent command, giving access to parent options like `--verbose`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "The application can then be invoked as:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Custom option completers, converters, and validators"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"Aesh supports custom implementations for tab-completion, type conversion, option validation, and more.\n"
"These implementations are CDI beans, so they can inject services:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Reference custom completers, validators, and converters via their class in annotation attributes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "CDI beans implementing aesh interfaces (`OptionCompleter`, `OptionValidator`, `Converter`, `CommandActivator`, etc.) are automatically kept by Arc even though they are only referenced from annotations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Completers can inject CDI services. This is particularly useful in console mode, where a completer can offer context-aware suggestions based on application state (e.g., completing task names from a service)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Mixins (reusable option groups)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"Mixins allow you to define a set of options in a separate class and reuse them across multiple commands.\n"
"Use the `@Mixin` annotation to include a mixin's options in a command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "The mixin class is a plain Java class with `@Option` fields. It does not need any annotations on the class itself."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Commands include the mixin with `@Mixin`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "The mixin's options (`--format`, `--verbose`) are added to the command as if they were declared directly on it. Tab completion and help output include them automatically."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Dynamic default values"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"You can provide dynamic default values for command options by implementing the `DefaultValueProvider` interface as a CDI bean.\n"
"The extension automatically discovers and applies it to all commands:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Register as a CDI bean. The extension discovers it automatically -- no additional wiring needed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Return `null` to use the annotation-declared default. Return a value to override it at runtime."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Per-command providers can also be specified via `@CommandDefinition(defaultValueProvider = MyProvider.class)`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Option features"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Allowed values"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"Restrict an option to a fixed set of values with `allowedValues`. Invalid values are rejected at parse time,\n"
"and tab completion automatically suggests the allowed values:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Fallback values"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"Use `fallbackValue` for three-state options where the option can be omitted, specified without a value,\n"
"or specified with an explicit value:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "`--debug` alone uses the fallback value `\"5005\"`. `--debug=8000` uses the explicit value. Omitting the option entirely uses the `defaultValue` (if set)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Customizing CLI settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "You can customize the underlying Aesh `SettingsBuilder` by implementing the `CliSettings` interface:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Multiple `CliSettings` beans can be registered. They are applied in arbitrary order, so avoid conflicting settings across implementations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Build-time validation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "The Aesh extension validates command configurations at build time. Invalid configurations are reported as deployment failures with descriptive error messages, so you can fix them before the application starts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "The following checks are performed:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "**Duplicate top-level command names** -- two or more top-level command classes with the same `@CommandDefinition(name = \"...\")` value."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"**Missing `@CommandDefinition` on group sub-commands** -- a class listed in `@CommandDefinition(groupCommands = {...})` that is not annotated with `@CommandDefinition`.\n"
"*"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Remote terminal access"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"The Aesh extension provides optional sub-extensions for remote terminal access via WebSocket and SSH.\n"
"These allow users to interact with your CLI application from a browser or an SSH client while the application is running in console mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "WebSocket terminal"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Add the `quarkus-aesh-websocket` dependency to expose a browser-based terminal:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Once added, the terminal is accessible at `http://localhost:8080/aesh/index.html` when the application is running."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"The built-in terminal page uses https://xtermjs.org/[xterm.js], which is bundled with the extension.\n"
"No external CDN or internet access is required."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "The WebSocket endpoint is registered at `/aesh/terminal` by default. You can change the endpoint path:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "The built-in HTML page connects to the default path. When using a custom path, access the page with a `path` query parameter: `http://localhost:8080/aesh/index.html?path=/custom/terminal`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "To disable the WebSocket endpoint:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "WebSocket authentication"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"The WebSocket terminal endpoint has no authentication by default. You can secure it by\n"
"requiring an authenticated user or restricting access to specific roles. Both options\n"
"require a Quarkus Security extension to be present (e.g., `quarkus-elytron-security-properties-file`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "To require any authenticated user:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "To restrict access to specific roles:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "When `roles-allowed` is set, `authenticated` is ignored since role-based access implies authentication."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"The extension will log a warning at build time if the WebSocket terminal is enabled\n"
"in production without authentication configured."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "SSH terminal"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Add the `quarkus-aesh-ssh` dependency to expose an SSH server:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Connect to the terminal with any SSH client:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Configuration properties:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"Password and public key authentication can be used simultaneously. When both are configured,\n"
"clients can authenticate with either method. If neither is configured, any password is accepted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"The extension will log a warning at startup if the SSH server is running without\n"
"any authentication configured (no password, no authorized-keys-file)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Connection management"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Both SSH and WebSocket transports support limiting concurrent sessions and closing idle connections."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "When `max-connections` is set, new connections beyond the limit are rejected immediately. When `idle-timeout` is set, sessions with no input activity for the specified duration are closed automatically."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Session events"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "The extension fires CDI events when remote sessions open and close. Use these to monitor session lifecycle, log access, or perform cleanup:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Events are fired asynchronously. Use `@ObservesAsync` (not `@Observes`) to receive them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "The `AeshSessionEvent` payload provides:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "`sessionId()` -- unique identifier for the session"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "`transport()` -- `\"ssh\"` or `\"websocket\"`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "`timestamp()` -- when the event occurred"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Events are fired for both SSH and WebSocket sessions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Health checks"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "When the `quarkus-smallrye-health` extension is present, readiness health checks are automatically registered for SSH and WebSocket transports. The health endpoints report whether each transport is running and the number of active connections."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "To disable the health checks:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Local console behavior with remote transports"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"When a remote transport extension (`quarkus-aesh-websocket` or `quarkus-aesh-ssh`) is present,\n"
"the local console (stdin/stdout) is **not started by default**. This means the application starts\n"
"as a normal Quarkus server, and CLI access is available only through the remote transport."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"This auto-detection prevents the local console from blocking the terminal when the application\n"
"is intended to run as a server with remote CLI access."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "You can override this behavior with the `quarkus.aesh.start-console` property:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "The auto-detection logic:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "No remote transport present -> local console **starts** (default CLI application behavior)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Remote transport present -> local console **skipped** (server mode with remote CLI access)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "`quarkus.aesh.start-console` explicitly set -> overrides auto-detection in either direction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Security considerations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"The WebSocket and SSH terminals provide remote access to your application's CLI.\n"
"In production, always configure authentication:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"**SSH**: Use `quarkus.aesh.ssh.authorized-keys-file` for public key authentication (recommended),\n"
"or set `quarkus.aesh.ssh.password` for password authentication (use `${SSH_PASSWORD}` to avoid\n"
"storing the password in plaintext). Both methods can be used simultaneously.\n"
"Without either, any password is accepted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"**WebSocket**: Set `quarkus.aesh.websocket.authenticated=true` or `quarkus.aesh.websocket.roles-allowed`\n"
"to require authentication. This requires a Quarkus Security extension."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"Additionally, restrict network access to these endpoints using firewalls or bind addresses.\n"
"Use `idle-timeout` to automatically close abandoned sessions and `max-connections` to limit concurrent sessions and prevent resource exhaustion. Health checks (when `quarkus-smallrye-health` is present) provide visibility into the number of active sessions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"WebSocket connections are not protected by the browser's same-origin policy.\n"
"If the WebSocket terminal is exposed on a network, consider configuring CORS via the\n"
"`quarkus.http.cors` settings to restrict which origins can connect."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Providing your own QuarkusMain"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"You can also provide your own application entry point annotated with `@QuarkusMain` (as described in xref:command-mode-reference.adoc[Command Mode reference guide]).\n"
"When a `@QuarkusMain` is present, the Aesh extension will not register its own runner."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Development Mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid ""
"In development mode (`mvn quarkus:dev`), the Quarkus dev console takes control of the terminal for its interactive features (live reload, test output, etc.).\n"
"This means the local terminal is not available for aesh CLI interaction."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "To test your CLI commands during development, you have the following options:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "**WebSocket terminal**: Add the `quarkus-aesh-websocket` dependency and access the CLI via browser at `http://localhost:8080/aesh/index.html`. The dev console stays on the local terminal while the aesh CLI runs in the browser."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "**Pass arguments**: Use `mvn quarkus:dev -Dquarkus.args='--help'` or `mvn quarkus:dev -Dquarkus.args='-n Quarkus'` to pass arguments directly. The application is re-executed every time the `Space bar` key is pressed. For Gradle projects, use `--quarkus-args`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "**Build and run**: Build the application with `mvn package -DskipTests` and run it directly with `java -jar target/quarkus-app/quarkus-run.jar <command> [options]`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Dev UI"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "The Aesh extension provides Dev UI pages accessible at `http://localhost:8080/q/dev-ui` when running in development mode. The Aesh card in the Dev UI offers up to three pages depending on which sub-extensions are present."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Commands page"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Always available. Shows a table of all discovered CLI commands with their name, description, type (Group or regular), class name, and sub-commands for group commands. The resolved execution mode (console or runtime) is displayed at the top. A search field allows filtering commands by name, description, or class name."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Sessions page"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Available when a remote transport extension (`quarkus-aesh-websocket` or `quarkus-aesh-ssh`) is present. Displays transport cards showing the status, active session count, and maximum session limit for each transport. Below the cards, a live event log shows session opened and closed events in real-time as users connect and disconnect."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Terminal page"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Available when the `quarkus-aesh-websocket` extension is present. Embeds an interactive terminal directly in the Dev UI using https://xtermjs.org/[xterm.js]. Click **Connect** to open a WebSocket connection to the terminal endpoint and interact with your CLI commands from the browser. The terminal supports the same features as the standalone terminal page (color, resize, unicode)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Packaging your application"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "An Aesh command line application is a standard Quarkus application and can be packaged as a JAR or a native executable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "As a jar"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Building an uber-jar is practical if you plan on distributing the JAR directly:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "As a native executable"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "You can build a https://quarkus.io/guides/building-native-image[native executable] for faster startup and lower memory usage:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "The Aesh extension automatically registers command classes and their option types for reflection in native builds."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/aesh.adoc
msgid "Configuration Reference"
